    <stitle>SINGLE REDUCTION CARRIERS: ROCKWELL - REASSEMBLE - INSTALL AND ADJUST THE THRUST SCREW</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="4">
        <title>INSTALL AND ADJUST THE THRUST SCREW</title>
        <para>If the carrier does not have a thrust block
            <ftnref xrefid="fn1400601"/>* start at Step 4.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate the carrier in the repair stand until the back surface of ring gear is toward the
                top.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Put the thrust block
                <ftnref xrefid="fn1400601"/>* on the back surface of the ring gear. The thrust block MUST be in the
                center between the outer diameter of gear and differential case.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate the ring gear until the thrust block* and hole for thrust screw, in carrier are
                aligned (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f14006d0">Figure 130</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f14006d0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g14006d0" filename="../figg14/G14006D0.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 130. Rotate Ring Gear</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HOLE FOR THRUST SCREW</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. THRUST BLOCK</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the jam nut
                <ftnref xrefid="fn1400601"/>* on the thrust screw
                <ftnref xrefid="fn1400601"/>*, one half the distance between both ends (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f14006d1">Figure 131</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f14006d1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g14006d1" filename="../figg14/G14006D1.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 131. Install Jam Nut and Thrust Screw</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the thrust screw
                <ftnref xrefid="fn1400601"/>* into the carrier until the screw stops against the ring gear or thrust
                block
                <ftnref xrefid="fn1400601"/>* (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f14006d1">Figure 131</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clearance between thrust screw or block and ring gear - .025 to .045 inch (.65 to 1.14 mm).
                Loosen the thrust screw 1/2 turn, 180&#176; (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f14006d2">Figure 132</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f14006d2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g14006d2" filename="../figg14/G14006D2.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 132. Loosen Thrust Screw</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten the jam nut
                <ftnref xrefid="fn1400601"/>* to the correct torque value against the carrier (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f14006d3">Figure 133</hotlnk>). Refer to the
                <hotlnk document="s14006t_57.xml" xrefid="hl1400608">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f14006d3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g14006d3" filename="../figg14/G14006D3.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 133. Tighten Jam Nut</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>To complete the assembly of axles equipped with driver controlled main differential locks,
                        refer to
                        <hotlnk document="s14006t_HL1400627.xml" xrefid="hl1400627">INSTALL DIFFERENTIAL SHIFT
                            ASSEMBLY</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
